.Sh NAME
.Nm vp
.Nd view image files 
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Fl fhlsvz
.Op Ar
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
View Picture
.Ar files
using SDL. Supported file types include jpeg, gif, png, bmp, ppm, xpm, pcx,
tga, and anything else your install of sdl_image supports. Keyboard controls
are escape or q to quit, f to toggle fullscreen, z to toggle scale-to-fit,
left arrow to go to the previous image, right arrow to go to the next image,
and space to toggle slideshow. n toggles the on-screen display of the current
file name, and N (shift-n) cycles its position through the corners, edge
centers, and screen center. The view can be zoomed with + and - (or the
keypad equivalents), or in larger steps with page up and page down; = returns
to 1:1, and shifted arrow keys pan a zoomed image. The mouse also controls
the view: dragging with the left button pans, the scroll wheel zooms at the
pointer, and dragging the middle button up or down zooms in or out (holding
the left and right buttons together works as the middle button). Zooming,
panning, or toggling fullscreen disables slideshow mode. File names starting
with http:// are interpreted as URL's and downloaded.
.Sh OPTIONS
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It Fl f, -fullscreen
Start in fullscreen mode
.It Fl h, -help
Show the help screen
.It Fl l, -loud
Loud behavior. Print out file names as it displays
.It Fl s, -sleep
Sleep time between images, in seconds. Fractions are accepted
(2.5 means two and a half seconds); the range is 0.1 to 60.
.It Fl r, -resolution
Screen resolution (for fullscreen). <width>x<height>@<bpp>
.It Fl v, -version
Print the version and exit
.It Fl z, -zoom
Scale images to fit the screen (zoom)
.El
.Sh ENVIRONMENT
.Bl -tag -width VP_RENDERER
.It Ev VP_RENDERER
Force the rendering backend, mainly for debugging or testing on machines with
or without 3D acceleration. Accepted values are
.Ar auto
(the default: use hardware acceleration if available, otherwise fall back to
the software renderer),
.Ar accelerated
(or
.Ar hw ;
hardware only, fail if unavailable), and
.Ar software
(or
.Ar sw ) .
With the
.Fl l
flag the selected renderer and whether it is accelerated are printed at
startup.
.El
.\".Sh DIAGNOSTICS
.\"Filenames are sent to stderr.
.Sh BUGS
Bad jpeg images force the program to exit.

